<span id="freeTextContainer11927288342571016607">When a middle-aged person finds themself enjoying a young adult fiction book just as much as, or more than they would have when they were a teenager, I think that says quite a bit about the quality of the story. Such was the case with me reading The Aureate Spectacles. I really loved reading this book, experiencing through the pages the adventures of Michaela and all the others in the story. And thanks to the author&apos;s expert use of intelligent, descriptive, rather poetic words, I found myself pu</span>
  <span id="freeText11927288342571016607" style="display:none">When a middle-aged person finds themself enjoying a young adult fiction book just as much as, or more than they would have when they were a teenager, I think that says quite a bit about the quality of the story. Such was the case with me reading The Aureate Spectacles. I really loved reading this book, experiencing through the pages the adventures of Michaela and all the others in the story. And thanks to the author's expert use of intelligent, descriptive, rather poetic words, I found myself pulling out my dictionary, I think almost once every chapter, to familiarize myself with new vocabulary, which in my opinion, is a good thing.</span>
